  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Caring and effiecient staff.&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Mrs A Tonks&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Having already had my left hip joint replaced, and now my right hip is giving pain and discomfort, especially when shopping. I was acutely aware of the symptoms, and that an X-ray was required to assess the joint state. Getting an appointment with my GP can take weeks. In the circumstances, I had little alternative but to try Hospital Accident and Emergency. The usual place for me to go in the past has been New Cross Hospital. The last time I visited there the waiting time was over four hours. I was not looking forward to that again so I turned to Russell Hall as it was, at least, easier for me to get to by car. Apart from the parking difficulty, I was pleasantly surprised how efficient your A&amp;amp;amp;E section was; everywhere very clean, the staff were helpful and pleasant. I got the x-ray I wanted, together with an explanation on the state of my hip joint, and a promise that the details would be sent to my GP. I could not have got better treatment, and the wait was not long. With the pressure A&amp;amp;amp;E hospital sections are under these days, especially directly after a Bank Holiday, I felt compelled to write a note of thanks.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
